# FLEET-253,


**Business Case,**


**Prio 1 Emergency [90.0],**


**Approved,**


**Version 02.00 - As user**

(fleet maintainer/manager) I want to regurlarly update the configuration (e.g. EIV, irf, part.irf files) of the

logger. This shall happen over the air, while I am sitting at the PC and the Device under Test is

somewere in world connectect to the IPEcloud via 4G. I update the configuration, because of ECU

updates, further adjustments on the measurement configuration, new trigger points, etc. As this is a

frequent task this should be possible as easy as possible.


**Wish scenario:**


**1) I open IPEmotionRT.UI**


**2) Log into the IPEcloud**


**3) Select the relevant Logger/Configuration**


**4) Change configuration**

5) IPEmotionRT:UI pushes the new configuration to the Logger via IPEcloud

6) Config change on logger is visible to the user (New/Actual logger configuration is reported via the live


**link.)**


**First Step:**

a) In a first step it is acceptable that configfile is changed offline in IPEmotionRT.UI and uploaded to the


**IPEcloud**

b) Therefore it shall be possible to download the configuration from the logger to the IPEcloud

c) IPEcloud push the config file to the data logger. e.g. Via the IPEuplink a file location is given to the

logger. From this location the logger downloads the config file.

d) It shall be possible to manually activate the new configuration (e.g. via sending a MEA stop/start


**command)**

e) In case the config file contains invalid items, it should be still possible to upload corrected

configurations without physical access to the data logger.


**Manual Config-file upload: User Interface**


**- Config file can be upload, by clicking on actual config. This can be done in the logger details page https:**

//ipe-cloud.web.app/project/648c1c84-259b-4a07-9d31-f5c521d9ad4d/vehicles , and/or in the

vehicle/logger page  of the workspace / Project https://ipe-

cloud.web.app/dashboard/logger/c0f66a18-5815-4ed0-b82d-aa8fc6f1f01a .

- An upload menu provides past config files for selection and a new file select from PC.

- History of config files shall be provided including What (Filename), Who, When, State, Activate at,

Action.

- New Configuration files are used by the logger as soon he interrupts its measurement. Therefore, the

status of the config file shall be displayed to the user (upload pending [e.g. logger offline], config


**uploading, config uploaded, config active on logger)**

- It shall be possible to "force" the configuration upload, by stop/start the measurement after upload was

sucessfull.

- Later: It shall be possible to activate the configuration file at a predefined date/time.


**Vision:**

Configuration Features of IPEmotionRT.UI are implemented inside the cloud and I do not need to install

RT.UI on my own PC.


# FLEET-382,


**Business Case,**


**Prio 2 Must [70.0],**


**Approved,**


**Version 02.00 - - As a user**

Iwant to troubleshoot the data logger and therefore analyse how the logger status did change over time.

(only telemtry signals, not realtime, only 1 signal at a time)


**On the Logger Details page (see also Page 1 - IPEtronik new (figma.com) ):**

- By clicking on "Logger Status" a y-t charts opens and displays the logger state over time. Duration can

be changed by the user.

# FLEET-497,


**Business Case,**


**Prio 3 Should [50.0],**


**Approved,**


**Version 02.00 - If MEA files**

are deleted they are stored in the trash bin. There they can be finally deleted.

1) New menu item: "Trash" similiar to Browse MEAs.

-> Files get a property deleted, user which deleted it, time when deleted, restore, delete immediatelly.

-> Files will be only displayed at Menu Trash (Not under Logger Details, MEA)


**2) Automatically Delete files from trash after 30 days**
